  {
    "id": "kp-4.5-01",
    "section": "4.5",
    "order": 1,
    "title": "Symmetry",
    "title_zh": "对称性",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "Symmetry describes how a shape can be transformed and still look the same.\n\n**Line symmetry** (Reflectional symmetry) occurs when a shape can be folded along a line so that the two halves match exactly. The fold line is the **line of symmetry**.\n\n**Rotational symmetry** occurs when a shape looks the same after being rotated by less than $360^{\\circ}$ around its center. The **order of rotational symmetry** is the number of times the shape looks the same in one full $360^{\\circ}$ turn.\n\nIn 3D, we look for **planes of symmetry**. A plane of symmetry divides a solid into two mirror-image halves.",
      "zh": "对称性描述了一个形状在变换后如何保持外观不变。\n\n**线对称 (Line symmetry)**（轴对称）是指一个形状可以沿一条线折叠，使两半完全重合。这条折痕称为**对称轴**。\n\n**旋转对称 (Rotational symmetry)** 是指一个形状绕其中心旋转小于 $360^{\\circ}$ 后看起来保持不变。**旋转对称的阶数 (Order)** 是形状在一周 $360^{\\circ}$ 旋转中看起来相同的次数。\n\n在三维空间中，我们寻找**对称面 (Planes of symmetry)**。对称面将几何体分成两个互为镜像的部分。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-symm-count",
        "label": "Identify symmetry in shapes",
        "label_zh": "识别形状的对称性",
        "description": "State the number of lines of symmetry or the order of rotational symmetry for a given shape.",
        "description_zh": "写出给定形状的对称轴数量或旋转对称阶数。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-symm-count",
        "question": "For a regular pentagon, write down:\n(a) the number of lines of symmetry\n(b) the order of rotational symmetry",
        "question_zh": "对于一个正五边形，写出：\n(a) 对称轴的数量\n(b) 旋转对称的阶数",
        "solution": "**Step 1:** For any regular polygon with $n$ sides, the number of lines of symmetry is $n$.\n(a) $5$\n**Step 2:** For any regular polygon with $n$ sides, the order of rotational symmetry is $n$.\n(b) $5$",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：** 对于任何有 $n$ 条边的正多边形，其对称轴数量为 $n$。\n(a) $5$\n**步骤2：** 对于任何有 $n$ 条边的正多边形，其旋转对称阶数为 $n$。\n(b) $5$",
        "source": "Adapted from 0580"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
